<p>Is there a way to use the <code>.like</code> sqlalchemy function to return everything?  </p>  <p>I've tried something like</p>  <pre><code>session.query(Foo).filter(Foo.Bar.like('%')) </code></pre>  <p>but this is returning only values that have a value in column Bar of Foo. I want to write a function that has a default keyword argument value of '%' or a wildcard so that it can be used to filter data as needed.</p>  <p>I have looked at the docs without success :(<a href="http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/rel_0_9/core/sqlelement.html#sqlalchemy.sql.operators.ColumnOperators.match" rel="nofollow">http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/rel_0_9/core/sqlelement.html#sqlalchemy.sql.operators.ColumnOperators.match</a></p>